Narok Farmers Are Expected To Receive A Boost In Their Crop Yield With The Introduction Of A Farm Weather Application By Yara East Africa. The Application Compatible With Smartphones Will Help Predict The Weather Patterns In Their Region Thus Helping The Farmers Make Decision An When To Plant Or Not.The 2 Million Kenyan Shilling Project Seeks To Promote Good Farming Practices And Food Productivity Amongst The Pastoralist Community Which Has Oftely Been Hit By Drought. Kenya Is The Second Beneficiary Of The Kes 2 Million Project After Ghana, An Initiative Started By Yara’s Global Ceo